title: Andromeda ‚Äì Amaliah
content:
Amaliah is a London-based DJ, producer and label head whose sets and productions draw from the depth of UK dance music with a playful, percussive edge; from rhythmic techno and tech house to leftfield oddities.

With growing influence and sets at iconic venues such as Panorama Bar, fabric, Nowadays, Lofi, Amnesia and Tresor, and major festivals including Dekmantel, Draaimolen, DGTL, Love International, Butik and Glastonbury, she‚Äôs become a sought-after DJ across Europe and the UK, having recently also completed her first tour in Asia and Australia.

As a producer, Amaliah has released on top labels including On Loop, Dekmantel Recordings, Tratratrax, Black Artist Database and Peach Discs. Amaliah is also the founder of Borne Fruits, a label and events series championing new and emerging talent that hosts a monthly Rinse FM show and has curated events at London venues including Pickle Factory, The Cause and Phonox.

With 2026 set to continue her ascent, Amaliah remains a standout voice in contemporary club culture.

title: ELEMENTS Chapter 1 - Water
content:
We‚Äôre launching Elements, a new monthly night on the first Thursday of every month. Each night revolves around a different element and we‚Äôre opening with Chapter 1: Water. 

This one‚Äôs all about pure fun: house music, colour, and a transformed space that feels a bit like a mini-festival. We're bringing that festival feeling indoors.
For the first chapter we‚Äôre turning one of Edinburgh‚Äôs newest venues into an underwater utopia! Blue tones, immersive projection, custom artwork and design. Just enough atmosphere to make this night special.
DRESS CODE: Wear something blue... a tee, shades, anything to help the room feel more connected! It doesn't have to be crazy but we reward those who go all out and want to dress up. 
Music on the night comes from Macka, a familiar name across Scotland‚Äôs house scene with sets from Sub Club and Cab Vol to Fly Open Air, Fly Ibiza. Macka comes off a sold-out London show, and has picked up support from Pete Tong, Ewan McVicar and Dam Swindle.

title: Import: Anop & Elfz
content:
IMPORT RETURNS FOR OUR FIRST EVENT OF 2026 

After a wee bear snooze (as opposed to a big bear snooze) Import is kicking the year off with a bang! Get ready to dance the winter blues off to some ethereal fast beats. Nightcore, Trance, Electro, Hyperpop and more - expect dreamy, bouncy, fun, hard tunes.

Headlining the event we have Dreamland head honcho Anop (he/they) joining us from Manchester to make their Edinburgh debut. They‚Äôve been doing bits in the hard dance scene and we can‚Äôt wait to see what they bring for us! We also have the lovely Elfz (he/him) joining us. Elfz has been a staple in the Scottish fast music scene as one of Edinburghs finest producers and DJs and we are so excited to bring him back to Sneaky‚Äôs! Having both produced for Nightcore 4 Total Sluts you can expect to be dancing from start to finish.

On support we are delighted to have Sickboy back with us to top off a night of truly iconic fast music dj‚Äôs, as well as your resident party starter Buckfast Barbie.

title: People's Disco Club w. DJ Paulette (Hacienda) + Toni McVey
content:
People's Disco Club presents
DJ PAULETTE (Hacienda)
+ Toni McVey

Friday 6th February
11pm - 3am
LIMITED CAPACITY

From the Hacienda to Ibiza, over 4 decades, Paulette has entertained on the international stage, been resident at some of the biggest clubs internationally and shared the decks with the world's top DJs. As a selector on the vein of disco to house she is pretty much the best out there - good times, good vibes, top tunes - that's how Paulette rolls.

THE CATEGORY IS ‚Ä¶ AWARD WINNING ‚Ä¶

Winner of the DJ Mag Top 100 Lifetime Achievement Award (November 2022) and the Keychange (PRS) Inspiration Award (Sound City April 2023), DJ Paulette is a highly regarded DJ across the UK and Europe, born and raised in (and still resident of) Manchester. Over a 30-year+ career, she has scaled the heights of dance music fame and hedonism playing disco, house and techno to huge crowds and in cool underground basements. She is a dj who is renowned for consistently ‚Äòsmashing‚Äô every set she plays. One of two women to have a regular monthly residency at the Hacienda, she went on to have residencies at Heaven and Ministry of Sound, before serving successful stints in Paris and Ibiza. She has a keen talent for reinvention and replicating excellence. She is known for her monthly radio shows with Reform Radio, Gilles Peterson‚Äôs Worldwide FM and has a Global Residency show produced in collaboration with The Radio Department that can be found on Apple Music. She is a regular presenter stand in for AFRODEUTSCHE and Craig Charles on BBC 6 Music. 

In Scotland, Paulette's appearance at Kelburn Garden Party back in 2022 still lives as one of the best DJ sets seen there.

Support from from local soul / disco selector Toni McVey.

title: Feel The Real: Craig Smith, Frederick
content:
On Saturday February 7th, Craig Smith returns to a residency in his home city alongside long time collaborator and Yoruba Records artist Frederick.

Craig Smith is known for his uncompromising attitude to the music he loves and has always refused to be categorised, preferring instead to be known for playing "quality dance music‚Äù, his sets are a testament to 30 years of telling stories through music.

Frederick is a music producer and DJ based in Edinburgh, he has refined his craft through the mentorship of Craig Smith over the past 15 years. In parallel his connection with Osunalde has deepened his understanding of rhythm, spirit and sound. 

Edinburgh's new 200 capacity basement club in the heart of the city, created by Paradise Palms, Kelburn Arts and The Gilded Balloon creates the perfect environment to lose yourself. Join Edinburgh's most welcoming dance-floor where true music lovers unite. 

Grab your tickets now to be a part of this deep, percussive journey.

content:
This is NOT a beginner workshop.

Our first masterclass in December showed us that there is an appetite amongst you all to interact with a variety of DJs and get to know their secrets.

EPiKA is a femme collective that brings the best techno to Edinburgh, while simultaneously promoting femme DJs.

See you there!

title: Shampain ‚Äì Millenium Madness Tour
content:
In the wake of his debut electronic album Millenium Madness, Galway DJ/Producer Shampain brings the sweaty circus that is the Millenium Madness tour on the road. Blending the weird, the mad and the wonderful - the tour will take place in selected intimate venues across the UK & Ireland, with a unique twist for each show, delivering a special experience to every city. 

Shampain is a Galway-born DJ and producer whose eclectic sets fuse ambient, bass-driven, club and cinematic elements. With more than a decade behind the decks, he has earned a reputation as one of the rare touring DJs whose path is built not on releases, but on a colorful music library, flawless mixing, and a distinctive persona. Now a key figure in Ireland's underground scene, Shampain continues to push boundaries with his unique sonic style. Shampain co-founded both VSN and G TOWN Records. He also directs the DIY operations at FREAK Magazine; an exciting art and music platform celebrating the weird and wonderful of the audio and visual worlds. Across his first two releases he has worked with acclaimed Irish artists Julie Dawson (Of Newdad) and Elaine Malone, along with underground icons Bethany and Rachel Trench.

MANTUA is an experimental music project by Elaine Malone (p√¥t-pot/GEIS). Influenced by environmental decline, symbolism in the form of Virgin Mary holograms and the decay of nature. Mantua's third album ‚ÄòGaltee Vitual Muse‚Äô released on Fort Evil Fruit is rooted in psychedelia, shoegaze and dream pop, but with a more lo-fi approach, delving into murkier subterranean depths. 

‚ÄòThere‚Äôs an instinctive rawness to Malone‚Äôs meditations on loss and longing, summoned with gusts of distorted guitar, quivering drones and metronomic drum machines.‚Äô - Anois Os Ard

‚ÄòDarkly uplifting and neo-hallucinogenic‚Äô - Wire

title: Cosmic
content:
Hey everyone! Cosmic is back after a long break, with Mothership returning to The Mash House on Friday, 13th February. As always, the night will feature psychedelic full-on grooves and progressive tech. We are thrilled to have, for the first time at Cosmic our local music producer Act One, (Boom Shanka Music). Jack is a renowned artist whose music frequencies are traveling all over the world, and last summer, he lit up the Boom Festival Dance Temple.
To help build up the energy, we‚Äôve invited Aurora, all the way from the north of Scotland. Stephen has been playing tunes since the beginning of the psytrance free party scene in Scotland, club promoter in Inverness and founder of Back to Goa . The main floor will kick off at 22:00 with resident Dj PsyUbik, who‚Äôll be playing a proggy set for the early dancers. The portal will open at midnight with a set by SwampStomp. We are happy to have Clavey for the first time playing her tribal proggy followed by a surprise act.
Decor and a full emerging UV environment will be set by the Cosmic Crew. Please bring your psychedelic dancing shoes, colorful body paints, and join us for another psychedelic ritual.

title: Fangs: Manuel Darquart
content:
Manuel Darquart returns to Edinburgh, carrying a long and loved connection to the city through shared dancefloors with Jacuzzi General. A long-standing pal and trusted collaborator, Manuel Darquart‚Äôs relationship with the city runs deep, rooted in late nights, mutual respect and a shared love for records that favour feeling over formula.

Known for a sound that drifts between hazy, psychedelic textures and Europe-leaning disco warmth, his selections and productions carry a sense of freedom and back alley Ibizan romance, equal parts cosmic and grounded. With releases on Wolf Music Recordings and a catalogue that includes Keep It DXy, Birds of Paradiso EP and The Del Sol EP, Louie has been building a well-earned reputation for music that is generous, emotional and deeply danceable.

title: ‚ô± 1 Year of Nightcore Rave ‚ô± Bongo Club ‚ô± Fri 20 Feb ‚ô±
content:
‡º∫ ùñìùñéùñåùñçùñôùñàùñîùñóùñä ùñóùñÜùñõùñä ‡ºª
One year ago we took a gamble on running Scotland‚Äôs first ever Nightcore Rave, thanks to your support we‚Äôre back celebrating its first birthday <3

Big love to all who came to last year's instalments, the fact we are able to run these niche subculture-focused parties is owed to you! After many requests it‚Äôs back on the 20th at Bongo to provide another dose ft. even more OG nightcore classix!

A genre whose humble beginnings started simply as sped-up pop songs with anime pictures as cover art, nightcore has since become one of the most influential aesthetics in recent years. Since its genesis in the early 2000s, artists like Fallen Shrine, S3RL, and labels like Nightcore for Total Sluts have developed the style into a genre in its own right.

What started as a celebration of niche internet microgenres is fast becoming the subcultural hub for Edinburgh‚Äôs alternative club scene and accelerated digital aesthetics ‚ú∞

Get ready for a night of pitch-shifted vocals and high BPMs celebrating the true Y2K10 aesthetic. Expect Happy Hardcore, Kandicore, Trance, J-Core, Kawaii Future Bass, Hyperpop and of course Nightcore.

title: EPiKA: Livid
content:
For our first EPiKA of 2026, we‚Äôre welcoming Livid - a DJ whose sound is as raw as it is refined: rolling rhythms wrapped in hypnotic elegance. Her sets feel like immersive rituals - shadowy atmospheres, driving percussion, and that slow-build intensity that pulls you deeper with every transition.

Originally from Rome and now embedded in London‚Äôs underground, Livid‚Äôs sound is fluid, magnetic, and unmistakably her own. Through her residency with Snooze, she‚Äôs been carving out a sonic identity built on consistency, depth, and an unwavering commitment to the craft, guiding dancefloors into deep, transformative states.

She‚Äôs promising us what EPiKA is about - some serious techno!

Do not miss this one!

title: LIKE THIS #021
content:
SAT.21.FEB  |  11PM-3AM
PEOPLES LEISURE CLUB
¬£5, ¬£10 ONLINE PRE SALES
MORE ON THE DOOR......

SPECIAL GUEST - LOVE IS BLIND

For years, London-based Love is Blind has been quietly shaping soundtracks for others. Operating behind the scenes, she‚Äôs been a driving force behind several indie record labels, curating, crafting and championing independent music.

Now stepping fully into the booth, she brings one simple rule: love songs only - romantic, dramatic, messy and made for dancing. Her groove-led, energetic sets celebrate love‚Äôs chaos - and encourages the occasional poor decision on the dancefloor.

A selector who takes love seriously enough to dance to it, but not seriously enough to behave.

LIKE THIS has solidified its place as a cornerstone of Edinburgh's underground scene over the past three and a half years. Digging from the rich history of dance music and cutting-edge sounds of today. Residents Lee Marvin, Jimmy Jammin' (Main Ingredient), and Marti-Time! (Unstable Creations) have cultivated a loyal following through their intimate monthly gatherings in Edinburgh Playing the diverse Festval scene and their international gigs in Berlin, Ibiza, Switzerland and beyond. Drawing inspiration from the iconic sounds of Chicago, Detroit, Berlin, New York and London.

LIKE THIS posses a profound understanding of dance floors. Their parties are a masterclass in musical curation: Raw and unfiltered beats with forward-thinking sounds that transcend eras. Each event is a journey back to a time before genres, evoking the spirit of the original underground parties in basements, garages, lofts, and warehouses where dance music culture was born. With an ever-evolving selection of fresh tracks from around the globe, LIKE THIS continues to push boundaries, creating an experience that is both current and deeply rooted in the essence of dance music history.

title: Live and In-store: Natasha Kitty Katt
content:
Umbrella Vinyl is thrilled to welcome the return of Natasha Kitty Katt to celebrate the release of her vinyl EP 'Cybernetique'.
Released in the twilight of 2025 on her own label, Shadowrunner Records, 'Cybernetique' features two dancefloor-ready powerhouses ‚Äî 'Cybernetique' and 'Neural Net' by the influential Edinburgh DJ and producer who's re-defining disco-house culture through a series of electrifying underground releases.
Forged in the flicker of a dystopian cityscape, these tracks pulse with the lifeblood of Neo Noir ‚Äî driving synth basslines, hypnotic arpeggios, and relentless electronic rhythms built for late-night floors and strobe-lit basements.
On side A, 'Cybernetique' captures the tension of a future metropolis in motion ‚Äî mechanical, seductive, and cinematic.
'Neural Net', on the flip, dives deeper into the circuitry, weaving emotion and machine in perfect sync.
Together, they form a twin narrative of dark euphoria and synthetic soul.
Nastasha will be in-store to greet fans and talk about her music Of course, we'll make sure she gets behind the decks to spin some vinyl from her collection.

title: Alien Disko: Tanukichi (Night On Earth / RAM Records / Undergroundtekno)
content:
Alien Disko returns to our residency at the Bongo Club on Friday 27th February with our first international booking of the year: the legendary Tanukichi!

Tanukichi is a Japanese DJ who‚Äôs always willing to evolve and to experiment at the frontiers of sound, in order to craft original tunes that strike powerful chords with his audience.

He has been into Europe‚Äôs free party culture since 2006, after a life-changing Teknival experience in his home country. Since then, he has been producing music that perfectly fits this scene‚Äôs vibe. Over the years he became one of the faces of European Hardtek, as well as being a trait d‚Äôunion between Japanese and European rave scenes.

Tanukichi‚Äôs vivacious sound, centered on powerful kick drums, big bass and steady rhythms, all matched with a pristine and flawless sound production, moves and contaminates the audience‚Äôs spirit in a chain of energy and entertainment.

He is currently trying to achieve an high-powered sound with 4 kicks and a 175 BPM pace, pioneering the next era of drum and bass, energising people and making them dance, feel, and fly on the high spirits of the kick bass, as has always been the case in Tanukichi‚Äôs 18 years long music career.

Tanukichi consistently performs at major festivals across Europe and Japan.
Among others, he has played: Boomtown Festival and Glastonbury in the UK, Fujirock in Japan, Defqon.1 Festival in the Netherlands, Electrobotik Invasion and  Reperkusound in France, Selvatek in Spain, Beats For Love Festival and X-Massacre in Czech Republic.

As a producer who's music is always a staple of our residents USBs, we are very excited to have Tanukichi for his Bongo headline debut! 

Joining Tanukichi in the booth we're delighted to announce that we have Jigsore's Karl Radox and Brockout's duo Rhythm Session venturing up north, who will be spanning 140-165bpm Acid, Jungle, and Breaks. Alien Disko residents will be completing the roster with our signature multi-genre style.

title: Samedia x Oi Musica: Dance Into Light feat. Jamz Supernova, El Buho & More
content:
Saturday 28th February
Samedia Shebeen & Oi Musica present

DANCE INTO LIGHT
DAY PARTY: 5pm - 11pm
With
Jamz Supernova (DJ Set)
El Buho (Live)
Oi Musica (Live)
+ Samedia DJs

Portobello Town Hall
Edinburgh

Plus: Samedia Decor / Decades of Dub Bar / Knights Kitchen African Food / Family Friendly

Legendary Edinburgh tropical party starters Samedia Shebeen join forces with street music promoters and educators Oi Musica for a very special one-off celebration in the heart of Portobello where both outfits are based.

Jamz Supernova (BBC 6music / DJ Set)
Jamz Supernova uses sonics to tell a story. The multi-faceted creative force is a label head, radio host, DJ, podcaster, and true tastemaker, broadcasting for over a decade. Known for her slots on BBC Radio 1Xtra (Best Specialist Aria Gold Winner 2021), BBC 6Music (Broadcast & Press Guild Best radio show of 2022) & Selector Radio for the British Council, reaching over 4 million global listeners. She is an avid explorer, collector and promoter of diverse worldwide sounds and frequently travels the globe to connect and understand musical movements at their source. As a DJ she weaves these thread together with style and skill and plenty of attitude to make a great dancefloor experience for all.

El Buho (Shike Shika / Live)
Robin Perkins aka El B√∫ho was born in the rolling hills of northern England but found his musical home in the forests, rivers & mountains of Latin America. His sound marries his influence of Dub, IDM and Electronica with the rhythms, traditions and melodies of Latin American folk and the organic sound of waterfalls, birdsongs and crackling leaves. The result is a dreamy, deep, melodic journey that entrances as much through headphones as it does on the dancefloor.

His breakthrough EP Cenotes, written whilst living in Mexico and featuring the track Ma√±ana Tepotzlan, was released in 2015 via Wonderwheel Recordings and was followed in 2017 by his debut album Balance to critical acclaim as one of the the leading names in the emerging organic electronic scene. 

Alongside his music, El B√∫ho is also an environmental activist, having worked for over eight years at Greenpeace, being a member of DJs For Climate Action and coordinating the non-profit project ‚ÄúA Guide to the Birdsong‚Äù a series of albums that raise funds and awareness for endangered bird species through electronic music. In 2020 he also participated in the New York Times author Ian Urbina‚Äôs project The Outlaw Ocean, creating a four track EP inspired by the ocean deep and the need to protect this mysterious, beautiful and fragile ecosystem from threats like oil drilling.

Oi Musica (Live)
Oi Musica creates visceral live performances using rhythm, percussion and brass. Their music is all about building energy and blurring the lines between audience and performer. They'll be debuting a brand new project with live brass & percussion, fat electronics and plenty of vibe! Drawing inspiration from global street band music, Oi Musica is guaranteed to bring the energy of hot dusty streets at carnival time right into the heart of the dance floor. Don‚Äôt miss the debut of Oi Musica‚Äôs freshest new act‚Ä¶

Samedia DJs
This crew have been rocking dancefloors across the UK and beyond for over 15 years with their exciting fusions of world and global club sounds. Known locally for their annual Solsctice Beach Party and long-running residency at the Mash House.

North Fire Soundsystem
Providing the bass, mids and tops all the way from Cumbria - one of the top soundsystems on the scene and long time collaborator with Samedia at Knockengorroch, Boomtown and beyond.

This event runs from 5pm - 11pm. Under 18s are welcome until 8pm.

Tickets on sale now!

title: Session Victim (LIVE) ‚•ä Lobos ‚•ä Hobbes ‚•ä Jedda ‚•ä Mixfits ‚•ä Geordie ‚•ä Maya Hacker ‚•ä Club_Nacht
content:
For our second guest of the season, we‚Äôre delighted to finally welcome a long-standing bucket-list booking and one of Germany‚Äôs most respected electronic acts.... Join us as Berlin‚Äôs Session Victim arrive in the Scottish capital for a very special live appearance on Saturday 28 February.

Renowned for pushing boundaries within house and electronic music, Session Victim describe themselves, with typical understatement, as a ‚ÄúTwo Man House Band‚Äù. It‚Äôs an fitting title given their sound is rich, warm, deeply musical and built on feeling and meaninful groove.

Hauke Freer and Matthias Reiling are widely regarded as one of the most accomplished house duos of their generation. Their catalogue includes three genre-defining triple LPs on UK tastemaker label Delusions of Grandeur, alongside the critically acclaimed Needledrop album for Night Time Stories: a release praised for its depth, musicality and reverence for dancefloor culture. Add to this over twenty vinyl-only EPs and a string of modern classics for labels such as Rhythm Section, Retreat and Pen & Paper, and their influence becomes difficult to overstate.

As performers, there are very few modern house acts who havee logged as much meaningful club time as our February guests. For nearly two decades now, the Berlin-based duo have been quietly - and sometimes not so quietly - left their mark on dancefloors across the globe, from sweat-soaked basements to some of the most respected clubs and festivals in electronic music (think Panaroma Bar, Fabric, De School, Corsica to name but a few!).

It‚Äôs this extensive, hard-earned road experience that gives Session Victim their unmistakable confidence behind the machines they use.

Don't miss this rare opportunity to catch them live in an indepdent club setting. Tickets on sale now!

title: feeo (live) at Pianodrome
content:
AD93 signee feeo comes to the Pianodrome on March 6th, touring her new album Goodness.

'One of the most breathtakingly beautiful albums of the year.' - Pitchfork

Feeo is the solo project of Theodora Laird, emerging from the London experimental improvisation scene. It's easy to get lost in Goodness' dense and cold soundscapes-- the album is a peculiar and tremendously compelling combination the Copenhagen sound-dream, girded with a real immersive dread, reminiscent of F# A# Infinity at full pelt.

Every track is a highlight, but pay particular attention to 'win!'. The simple refrain of 'we can figure this out' is manipulated endlessly by Laird's shapeshifting voice; taking on new meanings with each dip, pause and elongation of the phrase. It feels like a memory of a dub song, the drums breaking through from time to time but firmly outside of the song; sounds are processed until they're unrecognisable then buzz around like insects. Finally, there's a moment of air before it all collapses into muffled bass.

Since the Album's release in October it has been subject to a steady stream of praise: Achieving #6 on Pitchfork's electronic albums of the year, DJ Mag's top albums of 2025 and the Guardian's best new tracks along with countless glowing reviews in publications across the music world.

Support comes from Daksh.

No one turned away due to lack of funds, free and concession tickets available, email office@curvingtrack.com

title: Jitwam (DJ set): Free Time
content:
Shaped by over a decade of moving through London, NYC, and Australia, Jitwam‚Äôs soulful music has always resisted borders. 

The Indian-born creative has long been known for nomadically fusing psychedelic soul, jazz, and house into spiritually charged records. Since his debut ‚ÄúTJD001‚Äù in 2013, Jitwam quickly gained respect from tastemakers like Gilles Peterson and Moodymann, who included the EP‚Äôs  ‚ÄúKeepyourbusinesstoyourself‚Äù in the now iconic DJ-Kicks compilation; a move that sparked international attention and set Jitwam on a global trajectory. 

With a creative process that is both intentional and intuitive, he released his self-titled debut album, ‡§ú‡§º‡§ø‡§§‡§Æ ‡§∏‡§ø‡§π‡§Å, in 2017. This was followed by several EPs on his own imprint, The Jazz Diaries, and full-length albums Honeycomb (2019) and Third (2022). With over 100 million streams to date, Honeycomb remains a defining release in Jitwam‚Äôs catalogue. 

Jitwam stands, as always, as a rare connective tissue between club rhythms and spiritual introspection. All part of his lived experience, his forthcoming project "ALLIN" project draws equal parts from classic soul, Indian cinema, lounge jazz, and Detroit house, a music community he holds a profound affinity for.

title: Deep Excursions (Daytime): Maurice Fulton
content:
Excited to welcome the supremely talented Maurice Fulton from Tokyo for the 2nd daytime instalment following the very lively & well received launch party with Linkwood & Craig Smith in December.

Originally from the port city of Baltimore in the U.S., he is widely regarded as one of house music's true originals with a back catalogue of highly sophisticated productions. A somewhat elusive character, his musical foundations run deep ‚Äî shaped by disco, funk, soul and early hip-hop before becoming synonymous with house music in the early 90‚Äôs. As an extremely accomplished DJ, his sound is very much influenced by his background with his sets moving freely between house, disco, techno and left-field selections.

The intimate People's Leisure Club basement is the ideal setting to showcase his talents. 

Also excited to welcome Atjazz Record Company affiliated 'Peacey' to the lineup. In addition to being an all round top lad, he is, like Maurice Fulton, an extremely talented producer with a very impressive back catalogue of original productions and remixes whilst also being equally at home on the decks as he is in the studio.

Expect deepness and when it comes to Maurice Fulton, definitely expect the unexpected!

***Capacity limited to 200***

--------------------------------------------------------------------

Maurice Fulton Bio

Maverick production genius Maurice Fulton is a man of few words, who is more inclined to let his music do the talking. We know for certain that he comes from Baltimore in the USA and has been DJing since his early teens. Starting on Hip-hop and then moving on to House and Garage at various residencies across the US he played under his nickname DR Scratch.

Maurice began playing organ in church and drums in high school. So when he put his talent to making music it wasn‚Äôt long before he was using his skills to produce tracks with The Basement Boys and Ultra Nate. His most famous work was heard on Gypsy Woman by Crystal Waters, one of the most successful house tunes of the early ‚Äò90s.

Maurice went on to become highly prolific in his production work releasing tracks on various labels through the 90‚Äôs including Nuphonic and Warp in the UK. Often linked to contemporaries like Carl Craig, Derrick May and Frankie Knuckles, his textured sounds and complexity of production astounded many and grew him a loyal fan base. Some called it weird house others arty disco, his left of centre productions were always on the money.

In his more recent years he has been working for Tirk, Kathy Diamond and DFA. Maurice likes to be known first and foremost as a producer, though for those in the know, Maurice is also an extremely accomplished DJ. His sets are firmly routed in the Loft and Garage classics that gave New York City its clubbing heritage. These tracks often quietly edited to perfection by his own hand, and presented and eq‚Äôed to maximum effect on the dance floor.

Maurice Fulton is one of house music‚Äôs true originals and his enviable back catalogue will live long in a modern world of disposable downloads.

--------------------------------------------------------------------

title: Temporal - The 00s
content:
The timeline moves forward. Following the launch of our archival residency, Temporal returns to The Liquid Room to turn the page on the millennium. We continue our mission to document and relive the distinct eras of House.

As the world crossed into the new millennium, the sound of House evolved. For Chapter 2, we are moving from the raw roots of the 90s into the digital revolution and genre-bending energy of the 2000s. We aren't just looking for the superclub anthems; we are digging for the Electro-clash cuts, the French Touch gems, and the early Tech House records that redefined the dancefloor.

The Liquid Room was born in the 90s, but we grew up in the 00s. This was the decade where our walls soaked up the sweat of a changing scene. By bringing Temporal into this era, we are revisiting the nights that solidified our legacy as an Edinburgh institution.

Expect top-tier DJs and Selectors delving deep into the depths of your temporal lobe to bring the distinct, driving sound of 00s House back to the forefront.

title: Theo Kottis ‚•ä Good Coll B2B Hobbes ‚•ä DRUMA ‚•ä Club Cadence  ‚•ä Club_Nacht ‚•ä Hobbes Music
content:
This March, we‚Äôre delighted to welcome DJ, producer and long-time Rinse FM resident Theo Kottis back to Edinburgh, as he plays The Bongo Club for the very first time.

You‚Äôd have to be living under a rock not to know Theo. One of Scotland‚Äôs brightest exports, he‚Äôs long been a mainstay of the UK electronic music circuit and a trusted presence behind the decks, playing clubs and festivals across Europe. Despite his international reach, he remains deeply connected to the city‚Äôs club culture, regularly appearing at some of Edinburgh‚Äôs most respected parties.

Kicking off his DJ career at just eighteen, we first met Theo when he was throwing parties and co-running the electronic music‚Äìinfluenced clothing brand We Own alongside Marty Bell (Poolsuite) and Tom Ketley (Fly Open Air). Momentum built quickly: from grassroots parties across Scotland, the trio went on to bring BBC Radio 1‚Äôs Pete Tong to a sold-out Ocean Terminal Shopping Centre, before Theo secured a coveted main-stage slot at RockNess - Scotland‚Äôs largest festival after T in the Park - all within the space of a year.

Fast forward fifteen years and Theo has gone from strength to strength, taking his sound worldwide and playing clubs and festivals across Europe and beyond - from intimate basement rooms to major stages. Along the way, he‚Äôs amassed millions of streams through a steady run of releases on labels including Dekmantel, Fabric, FUSE, CWPT, Moda Black and Permanent Vacation, alongside remixes for artists such as Sasha, Goldfrapp, Joe Goddard (Hot Chip) and Shadow Child. 

Never fixed to one side, Kottis' sound has evolved, while remaining underground and consistently ahead of the curve.

title: Ralph Lawson: Free Time x solescience
content:
Free Time is Sneaky Pete's Sunday 6-10pm DJ series with legendary and breaking artists
___________________________________________ 

Ralph Lawson has played a huge role in electronic music as a DJ, producer, founder of 20/20 Vision, original resident DJ at the legendary Back to Basics club night and founder member of 2020 Soundsystem. Through it all Lawson has stayed true to the original spirit of acid house and retained a love of cutting-edge underground music in a multi-award career spanning over three decades. 

Alongside Basics, Lawson has maintained long-standing DJ residencies at The Loft Barcelona, Space Ibiza and appeared regularly at fabric London since its inception ‚Äì as well as The Hacienda, Sub Club, DC10, Warehouse Project, Watergate and Panorama Bar. Lawson is also no stranger to big festival stages with performances at Sonar, Glastonbury, Love International, Houghton, Robot Heart, Burning Man, Electric Elephant, Hideout, Festival No.6, Lovebox, The Garden, Gottwood, Bluedot, Beatherder among many others.

Lawson has been behind many iconic productions over the years, often working in the studio alongside Carl Finlow, including their classic series of remixes for Blaze including ‚ÄòLovelee Dae‚Äô and the seminal ‚ÄòRaptures of the Deep‚Äô, both widely regarded as classic moments in house music. Lawson also collaborated with Detroit‚Äôs Chez Damier on several releases for Prescription Underground before co-founding 2020 Soundsystem, a pioneering band that fused electronic beats with live musicians and produced the highly acclaimed albums ‚ÄòNo Order‚Äô and ‚ÄòFalling‚Äô which garnered the club hits ‚ÄòSliding Away‚Äô ‚ÄòOcean‚Äô and ‚ÄòPsycho‚Äô.

title: Roni Size x LTJ Bukem
content:
Two absolute legends in the game, LTJ Bukem and Roni Size, join forces for a double headline show of mind-blowing drum ‚Äòn‚Äô bass.

Emerging out of the late 80‚Äôs as a DJ, LTJ Bukem discovered his passion for drum and bass when exploring the realms of jazz fusion. So it‚Äôs natural that when Bukem‚Äôs career as a DJ progressed in the early 90‚Äòs and he found himself delving in to the studio, it was these frantic breakbeats in tandem with the melodic, yet almost awry bass lines of jazz instrumentation that informed Bukem‚Äôs creations, developing a progressive and textured sound equal parts anthemic and tranquil. The album was titled ‚ÄòLogical Progression‚Äô and marked Bukem as an innovator, a tag that has stuck through his work on his own esteemed Good Looking Records imprint, and still bears strong today as Bukem continues to DJ extensively across the globe

Bristol native Roni Size is one of the U.K. jungle scene‚Äôs most respected names, with production credits spanning dozens of labels, projects, and releases. Although not as quick to rise to acclaim (either critical or popular) as peers such as Goldie or LTJ Bukem, Size‚Äôs influence as a producer, label owner, and committed underground magnate figured him as one of the emerging sound‚Äôs true pioneers. The breakout success of his debut album New Forms (including Britain‚Äôs prestigious Mercury Award) finally confirmed his stature and vaulted him to a greater degree of popularity than any other drum ‚Äôn‚Äô bass producer.

title: Bongo Incognito : Secret Special Guest
content:

title: Resurrection
content:
Celebrate the greatest event in history!

Join us for RESURRECTION, an event that has become an Easter tradition in Scotland, where Christians from across the central belt come together to celebrate the resurrection of Jesus through a powerful evening of music and worship.

Held annually in the iconic Usher Hall, home to the world-renowned Edinburgh Festival, this event is a joyous proclamation of the central truth of the Gospel: Christ is risen.

Led by the Origin Scotland band, choir, and orchestra, RESURRECTION unites believers from all denominations in a time of heartfelt praise and worship. It's more than just a concert; it's a gathering of the Church, where voices rise as one in celebration of the hope and victory we find in the resurrection of Jesus.

Join us this Easter Sunday for an evening that will renew your faith, fill you with joy, and unite us all around the greatest truth of our faith. Let the music move you, the message inspire you, and the atmosphere uplift you as we declare to the world the glory of the risen Christ.

Known for his infectious, groove-heavy percussion and signature vocal-led Tech House, Tre‚Äôs sound is built for the sweat-soaked walls of an institution like ours.

This isn't just about the headliner; it‚Äôs about the community. These artists will be digging deep to set the pace, ensuring the energy remains driving and distinct from the first beat to the last.

Expect a masterclass in the groove as we delve into the depths of your temporal lobe to bring the soul of modern House back to the forefront.

title: Terminal V Festival 2026
content:
Scotland's No. 1 electronic music festival, Terminal V Festival returns on April 18 + 19th 2026 with their much anticipated festival format‚Ä¶

Marking two epic days in the Scottish capital alongside 40,000 ravers and six fully immersive indoor and outdoor stages, the weekend is set to shake the foundations of Edinburgh's Royal Highland & Showground thanks to its diverse lineup which spans the spectrum of techno & beyond. Think new faces, fast rising talent and returning favourites.

Over 100 artists from every corner of the globe will be touching down in Edinburgh for the momentous occasion. Every stage will offer it's own standalone world, with bespoke architecture, mind-bending visuals and chest-rattling sound for a sensory experience built for those who live and breathe dance music.

Sara Landry brings the UK debut of her ETERNALISM show, her only Scottish appearance all year, while the likes of Klangkuenstler brings his unmistakable schranz sound back to the country for the first time since 2022 - a rare UK appearance.

Also joining the lineup is I Hate Models who marks a highly anticipated return alongside the likes of Clara Cuv√©, Ben Hemsley, Robert Hood, Novah, Fantasm, Sant√∏s, Patrick Mason, Vieze Asbak, East End Dubs, Patrick Topping, Mall Grab, Morgan Seatree, Klofama + MANY more.

Full day and stage splits have now been revealed for the festival. Each stage is designed with a clear purpose, allowing different parts of the electronic spectrum to exist without compromise, from peak-time headline techno to foundational house, from high-pressure intensity to emerging local voices.
 
Alongside a multi-faceted lineup and the addition of an extra 6th stage, a landmark ¬£1 million investment into site development and production upgrades is in place for 2026. Following feedback, this is a transformative step designed to elevate every aspect of the festival experience. These improvements will roll out across all stages, facilities and audience areas and underpin Terminal V‚Äôs continued rise as one of Europe‚Äôs leading large-scale electronic music festivals. 

Consistently ranked among DJ Mag‚Äôs Best Festivals in the World, Terminal V continues to evolve at a pace matched only by the scene itself, which is why 40,000 people from all over the world travel in numbers to the festival.

Potpourri invites their biggest headliners to date to the Sneaky Pete‚Äôs sweatbox. Edinburgh‚Äôs favourite experimental queer night welcomes G Jones & Eprom + Parkinson White to the booth. Potpourri‚Äôs High Beams, our custom club lighting rig and a signature hand-made incense scent will, of course, be there too!

When G Jones and Eprom collide, the result is a masterclass in sound design and raw energy. Touring in support of their latest collaborative work, Disk Utility, the duo fuses jungle, acid, and techno into a high-octane dismantling of the traditional DJ set. From the glitch-laden eruptions of "1000 Cuts" to the club-ready euphoria of "By Your Side," witness two of bass music‚Äôs most forward-thinking minds pushing the dance-floor into uncharted territory.

title: Hobbes Music 13th Birthday: Michelle Manetti ‚•ä Mairi B b2b Hobbes + many more ‚•ä Club_Nacht
content:
Join us this April as Hobbes Music marks 13 years in the game. We‚Äôre celebrating properly at The Bongo Club, with special guest and label alumnus Michelle Manetti.

DJ, vocalist, producer and promoter Michelle Manetti has deep roots in UK club culture. Cutting their teeth as an underage raver in the late 90s, they‚Äôve since become a respected figure in East London‚Äôs queer underground, bringing over 20 years of experience behind the decks and a reputation built on consistency, taste and graft rather than hype.

A committed advocate for marginalised and under-represented artists, Michelle is the founder of the FLINTA*-focused party F√®mmme Fra√Æche at Dalston Superstore, a long-running bi-monthly celebrating 10 years this year, known for safe space, strong line-ups and a genuine sense of community. They‚Äôve also held residencies at The Cause and Adonis, with regular appearances at Horse Meat Disco, Little Gay Brother, Homoelectric, Percolate and beyond.

More recently, Michelle has been working closely with Demi Riquisimo, with releases including the No Given Time EP and the 2023 standout ‚ÄúAll I Need‚Äù, a track that‚Äôs done the rounds and will already feel familiar to many. If it‚Äôs not already in your listening pile, now‚Äôs the time to fix that. Track below! 

Michelle was also previously the vocalist in cult London trio The Off Key Hat, who released a slew of head-turning records via Andy Blake's legendary vinyl-only label, Dissident (late 00s), including the bona fide club hit, Emergency Calling. MANY moons later, a pair of stellar demos landed at Hobbes Music hq and the label released the killer double A-side single, Shot At Dawn b/w Warm Your Love, in 2018.  

Michelle last visited Bongo when they co-headlined the HM label's 5th birthday with Glasgow's adopted Slovenian star (and fellow HM-alumnus), Nightwave. Suffice to say, Michelle's closing set absolutely tore the roof off the joint and they went on to deliver the goods again the following night at Paradise Palms.  Suffice to say, we've been working on a return date for some time...

Support duties on the night come from HM label boss Hobbes, going back-to-back with Mairi B to mark the label anniversary in proper fashion. Making the trip up from Newcastle, Mairi is one half of label affiliates Accident Machine, as well as a fierce selector in her own right.

Additional support acts are still to be announced, with more names landing soon.

title: RIVAL CONSOLES
content:
One of the UK‚Äôs most influential creators of electronic music, Rival Consoles, returns with a brand new audio-visual live show, centred around his new album Landscape from Memory ‚Äî marking a new chapter in an ongoing quest for refinement and evolution.

London-based producer Ryan Lee West, better known under the name Rival Consoles, is notable for making synthesisers sound human and atmospheric. Over the course of a critically acclaimed eighteen-year career, his music has diversified from the challenging electronic output of his early EPs, to gradually becoming more conceptual and metamorphic with his albums.

In July 2025 Rival Consoles released his latest studio album Landscape from Memory on Erased Tapes, and is presenting it with a brand new unique performance that will take the form of an immersive audio-visual experience in which he will present material from across the last 15 years of his career and beyond. From deep ambient works to his unique version of techno, and traversing the vast spectrum in between, the show will be a long-form narrative of ideas ‚Äî many heard live for the first time ‚Äî with visuals co-created and performed live by Sky Ainsbury.

‚ÄúImpossible to ignore, and hard to forget‚Äù ‚Äî Pitchfork ‚ÄúAmbient leaning, mind expanding electronics‚Äù ‚Äî DJ Mag

This show is 14+ / Under 16's admitted with adult

title: Max Cooper
content:
Max Cooper is an electronic composer, multi-disciplinary artist, music label founder and former scientist who has carved out a unique space in music and visual art.

 

He holds a PhD in computational biology at the same time as being the first contemporary electronic musician to perform at the ancient Acropolis theatre in Athens and one of the first clutch of musicians to produce in Dolby Atmos.

 

Cooper has enquired for over 15 years through music, collaborations, and his label Mesh, to explore the intersections between the arts and sciences with installations, performances, immersive experiences, online media, music videos and live events. Anchored throughout is his emotive approach, connecting how ideas and forms feel, in a manner accessible to us all.

 

"I've always had a strong emotive bond with aesthetics, and found at an early age that the purified forms of electronic music carried a lot of weight for me, as did the reductive natural aesthetics of the sciences. That felt connection to both opened up a world I've been lost in ever since."


Pivoting from computational biology to electronic music might not seem like the most natural career transition, but for Cooper the commonalities are obvious:"In both fields, you're in a sense, free. Free from the limits of living systems, free from the limits of corporeal sound. The only constraints are in your mind."



Max Cooper has collaborated with Zaha Hadid Architects, Dolby, L-Acoustics, 4DSOUND, Barbican Centre, W1 Curates, The Babraham Institute and exhibited work at museums including the Pompidou Metz, ZKM Karlsruhe, Museum Wave Seoul and The Science Museum London.

title: DAYS
content:
Tickets on sale February 2nd

------------------------------------------------------------------

DAYS returns to the Granton waterfront this May. We‚Äôre heading back to The Pitt Market, taking over the warehouse and yard for our best party to date (hopefully).

We‚Äôve been piecing this lineup together for a while, and the result is a proper cross-section of the sounds we‚Äôre into right now. We‚Äôve got the heavyweights covered with Daniel Avery, DJ Seinfeld, and Helena Hauff, while Sweely brings his signature live energy. Rounding things out are Papa Nugs and MarcelDune, two selectors currently at the top of their game.

As always, the local scene is the backbone of the festival. We‚Äôve invited a massive stack of talent from Edinburgh and further afield to make sure the energy is right from the very first set.

title: Start Of Summer Shindig: OOFT! ‚•ä Ann Tweak ‚•ä Hobbes ‚•ä Cosmico + more ‚•ä Club_Nacht
content:
Summer officially starts here. On Saturday 20th June, ahead of the summer solstice, we‚Äôre pleased to welcome back our Start Of Summer Shindig, this time with a very special guest: OOFT!.

A true mainstay of Scotland‚Äôs underground for well over a decade, OOFT! (aka Ali Herron) has earned his reputation through consistently strong parties, releases and DJ sets rooted in house, disco, funk and Balearic sounds. A DJ first and foremost, his approach is musical unflashy, and forever in the know.... the kind of selector who knows how exactly to let a record breathe.

As a DJ he has held long-running residencies at some of Glasgow's top venues including theThe Sub Club, The Berkeley Suite and, more recently, weekly Sundays at La Cheetah for his KEEP ON residency with fellow Gtown veteran David Barbarossa. Beyond Glasgow, he‚Äôs toured extensively across the UK, Europe and further afield, bringing a sound that comfortably moves from slow-motion Balearic moods through underground disco to classic, soulful house.

In the studio, OOFT! has built a deep and varied catalogue, releasing on respected international labels and carving out a reputation for music that DJs actually play. His 2012 track 'Love & Soulsaving' became something of a modern underground classic moving effortlessly through DJ bags worldwide, clocking up close to three and a half million streams and selling out its vinyl run, copies of which now regularly fetch serious money second-hand.

Since the release of his debut album Intricacies Of Modern Life in 2018, the focus has shifted. While original productions continue, much of his studio time is now spent crafting bespoke edits, reworks and tweaks - tools designed purely for the dancefloor. Many are cut exclusively for his own sets, tested in the moment and never released publicly. It‚Äôs this behind-the-scenes graft - the quiet refinement of records you didn‚Äôt know you needed - that keeps OOFT! firmly in demand and endlessly trusted behind the decks.

title: Bongo Closing Party ‚•ä Special Guest TBA
content:
We're delighted to be hosting Bongo Club's official closing party this year before they close to become a fringe venue over summer.

Join us as we power up the Danley PA system one more time before we return with our next guest series come September. 

Tickets on sale now!
